  "prompt": "Which is more acidic phenol or paranitro phenol?",
  "response": "P-Nitrophenol is more acidic than phenol. This is because the nitro group (-NO\u2082) is an electron-withdrawing group, which stabilizes the negative charge on the phenoxide ion formed after losing a proton. This stabilization increases the acidity of p-nitrophenol compared to phenol itself, which lacks such an electron-withdrawing group to stabilize its phenoxide ion.",
